Hunadi Mateme has served as the ANC's chief whip in the NCOP since coming to Parliament after the 2014 general elections. CAPE TOWN - The African National Congress (ANC) chief whip in the National Council of Provinces (NCOP) has resigned.NCOP chairperson Thandi Modise made the announcement at the start of its plenary sitting on Thursday afternoon. Before I proceed, I would like to announce that I have received a letter of resignation from the honourable Dr HE Mateme as chief whip of council. Modise says Dr Hunadi Mateme s replacement will be elected at a later point during the sitting.Mateme has served as the ANC's chief whip in the NCOP since coming to Parliament after the 2014 general elections.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)